text: "Nothing Compares 2 U" is a song written by Prince for his side project The Family for their debut studio album The Family and was made famous by Irish singer Sinéad O'Connor for her second studio album I Do Not Want What I Haven't Go. It was a worldwide hit, going to number 1 in many places. It was nominated for 3 Grammy Awards in 1991. ==Track listings== * 7" single # "Nothing Compares 2 U" – 5:09 # "Jump in the River" – 4:13 * CD maxi # "Nothing Compares 2 U" – 5:09 # "Jump in the River" – 4:13 # "Jump in the River" (instrumental) – 4:04 ==References== Category:1990 songs Category:1990s ballads Category:Pop ballads Category:Sinéad O'Connor songs Category:Prince (musician) songs Category:The Chicks songs Category:Chris Cornell songs Category:Blue-eyed soul songs
